; TUPLECMP simplification, constant join pivot: bar contributes the constant
; 1 and baz is a union of the constant fact 1 and message-fed rows. The join
; pivot compares the constant against the union column; the compare over the
; RED... constant arm must fold while message rows are compared at runtime.

#message m(i32 A).
#local bar(i32 A).
#local baz(i32 A).
#query foo(free i32 A).
bar(1).
baz(1).
baz(A) : m(A).
foo(A) : bar(A), baz(A).
